dynasty /ˈdɪnəstɪ/

(dynasties) 

1. N-COUNT A dynasty is a series of rulers of a country who all belong to the same family. 王朝 

例： The Seljuk dynasty of Syria was founded in 

1094. 叙利亚的塞尔柱王朝建立于1094年。 

2. N-COUNT A dynasty is a period of time during which a country is ruled by members of the same family. 朝代 

例： ...carvings dating back to the Ming dynasty. …可以追溯到明朝的雕刻。 

3. N-COUNT A dynasty is a family which has members from two or more generations who are important in a particular field of activity, for example, in business or politics. 世家 

例： This is a family-owned company – the current president is the fourth in this dynasty. 这是一个家族企业–现任总裁是该世家的第4代。

